SIMPLE: fervent
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fervent
<hw>Fer"vent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>fervent</ets>, L. <ets>fervens</ets>, <ets>-entis</ets>. p. pr. of
<ets>fervere</ets> o the boiling hot, to boil, glow.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Hot; glowing; boiling; burning; <as>as, a <ex>fervent</ex>
summer</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The elements shall melt with <qex>fervent</qex> heat.</q>
<rj><qau>2 Pet. iii. 10.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Warm in feeling; ardent in temperament; earnest;
full of fervor; zealous; glowing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Not slothful in business; <qex>fervent</qex> in spirit.</q>
<rj><qau>Rom. iii. 11.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>So spake the <qex>fervent</qex> angel.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A <qex>fervent</qex> desire to promote the happiness of
mankind.</q> <rj><qau>Macaulay.</qau></rj></p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Fer"vent*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Fer"vent*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Laboring <qex>fervently</qex> for you in prayers.</q>
<rj><qau>Col. iv. 12.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fervescent</ent>⟦br⟧
